Three Soldiers Killed in Turkey Land Mine Blast, AA Says

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-28T11:19:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/three-soldiers-killed-in-turkey-land-mine-blast-aa-says.html
A land mine blast in southeastern
 Turkey  killed three soldiers and wounded two others today, the
state-run Anatolia news agency reported.  The blast occurred as a military convoy was passing in the
town of Semdinli, the agency reported citing the governor of
Hakkari province, Muammer Turker.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  